properties.value: [format('Server={0}; Database={1}; User=appUser; Password={2}', reference(resourceId('Microsoft.Sql/servers', toLower(take(concat('sqlserver', uniqueString(resourceGroup().id)), 24))), '2020-11-01-preview').fullyQualifiedDomainName, 'db', parameters('appUserPassword'))]

properties.scriptContent:
wget https://github.com/microsoft/go-sqlcmd/releases/download/v0.8.1/sqlcmd-v0.8.1-linux-x64.tar.bz2
tar x -f sqlcmd-v0.8.1-linux-x64.tar.bz2 -C .
cat <<SCRIPT_END > ./initDb.sql
drop user ${APPUSERNAME}
go
create user ${APPUSERNAME} with password = '${APPUSERPASSWORD}'
go
alter role db_owner add member ${APPUSERNAME}
go
SCRIPT_END
./sqlcmd -S ${DBSERVER} -d ${DBNAME} -U ${SQLADMIN} -i ./initDb.sql
